BASENAME(1)                 User Commands                 BASENAME(1)

NAME
       basename - strip directory and suffix from filenames

SYNOPSIS
       basename PATH [SUFFIX]
       basename -s SUFFIX PATH...
       basename -a PATH...

DESCRIPTION
       Print the filename portion of PATH, with any leading directory
       components removed. If SUFFIX is specified, it is also removed
       from the end of the filename.

OPTIONS
       -a         Support multiple arguments
       -s SUFFIX  Remove SUFFIX from each name

EXAMPLES
       basename /usr/bin/cat
              Prints: cat

       basename /home/user/file.txt .txt
              Prints: file

       basename -s .json config.json data.json
              Prints: config
                      data

SEE ALSO
       dirname(1)
